Package javelin.model.world.location.town.labor

Class Labor

  • java.lang.Object
    • javelin.model.world.location.town.labor.Labor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Build, BuildRoad, Cancel, Deforestate, Growth, Redraw, Trait
    public abstract class Labor
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    Represents a card that can be used to progress a Town's district. Initially each labor is an empty placeholder inside a LaborDeck. Upon drawing they are cloned and the clones defined as actual cards via #define(Town). The suggested value for cost is 5/10/15/20 for weak/medium/powerful/epic labors.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
